[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    199[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"Cohort-stratified accuracy and family-experience monitoring uses the cohort-axis-hash labels rather than the underlying axis values; the cohort-axis-hashes are non-reversible by construction. Recipe-specific cohort axes: geographic-region cohort hash (rural-versus-urban; cross-jurisdictional-overlay-applicable; deaths-in-jurisdictions-with-slower-vital-records-feeds); age-decade cohort hash; sex-or-gender cohort hash, populated only from patient-consented self-identification; language-preference cohort hash for personal-representative-experience metrics; name-tradition cohort hash; source-mix cohort hash (deaths recognized through high-quality sources versus low-quality sources versus claims-cessation-inferences only); jurisdictional-overlay cohort hash (states with stricter posthumous-protection rules; states with diverging family-reported-death intake practices). Metrics: (a) per-cohort mean-time-to-recognize-death (computed monthly with rolling-window-baseline comparison); (b) per-cohort false-positive-death rate (sampled audit, computed monthly); (c) per-cohort false-negative-death rate (sampled audit, computed monthly); (d) per-cohort family-correspondence-after-death rate per 1000 deaths (incident-driven, computed weekly); (e) per-cohort cross-system-propagation-completeness rate within 24 hours (computed weekly); (f) per-cohort premature-death-report-reversal latency (computed per reversal); (g) per-cohort personal-representative-record-request completion time (computed per request); (h) per-cohort hidden-duplicate-revelation rate per 1000 death events (computed monthly). Disparity calculation: absolute difference between the cohort with the highest rate and the cohort with the lowest rate, computed per-metric per-cycle. Alarm thresholds: mean-time-to-recognize-death disparity > 30 days = MEDIUM; family-correspondence-after-death-rate disparity > 100 incidents per 1000 deaths = HIGH (because family-correspondence-after-death is the most family-visible signal of the institution's deceased-patient-resolution discipline and is a fairness signal at population scale); false-positive-death-rate disparity > 0.005 = HIGH (because false acceptances produce wrong-record disclosures that the consumer cannot retract); cross-system-propagation-completeness disparity > 0.10 = MEDIUM; premature-death-report-reversal-latency disparity > 3 business days = HIGH (because the affected patient experiences the disruption during the reversal interval); personal-representative-record-request-completion-time disparity > 5 business days = MEDIUM. Alarms route to the analytics governance committee, the equity-monitoring committee, the privacy team (which has explicit posthumous-protection-evaluation authority for this recipe), the patient-experience and patient-advocacy functions (which have explicit family-experience-evaluation authority for this recipe), and the institutional governance committee for cross-jurisdictional posthumous-protection overlays (for cross-jurisdictional-overlay-affected cohorts), with a 5-business-day SLA for the first investigation report. The post-mortem and any remediation (per-cohort source-coverage analysis, per-cohort matching-tolerance tuning, per-cohort family-reported-death-intake-quality analysis, per-cohort personal-representative-experience review, per-cohort cross-system-propagation analysis) is documented in the cohort-disparity ledger and reviewed quarterly by the deceased-patient-resolution-program steering committee with privacy-team and patient-experience co-chairs. The multi-dimensional-interpretation translation is explicit: cohort-disparity metrics in this recipe are simultaneously fairness signals, family-dignity signals, quality-measurement-bias signals, and framework-compliance signals; cohorts with anomalously high mean-time-to-recognize-death experience worse longitudinal-record-completeness and disproportionately receive wrong-patient correspondence in the post-death window; cohorts with anomalously high family-correspondence-after-death rate experience disproportionately the family-dignity-affecting impact; cohorts with anomalously high false-negative-death rate remain in quality-measure denominators they should be excluded from biasing the quality-measurement scores. The privacy team's posthumous-protection-evaluation, the patient-experience response-authority, the equity-monitoring response-authority, and the institutional governance response-authority are the authoritative determinations on whether a cohort-disparity event requires program-level-engagement (escalation to the deceased-patient-resolution-program steering committee, multi-disciplinary review with named ownership, framework-engagement) in addition to local-tolerance-tuning."[38;2;180;142;173m*[K
